message: "If you use this study, harness, or data, please cite it as below."
title: "Different Teachers, Different Capabilities: Sub-1B On-Device Distillation for Structured Text Enrichment"
authors:
  - family-names: Chaganti
    given-names: Vinay Kumar
    email: cvk.atreya@gmail.com
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/socraticsurge/distill-locally"
license: MIT
date-released: 2026-07-02
keywords:
  - knowledge distillation
  - small language models
  - LLM-as-judge
  - on-device inference
  - summarization
  - structured output
abstract: >-
  Study distilling an 8B reasoning teacher (DeepSeek-R1:8b) into a 0.6B student
  (Qwen3-0.6B) for structured text enrichment (free-text summary, five categorical
  labels, open-set topics), evaluated per sub-task against two non-distillation
  baselines and two teacher controls with a blinded three-judge LLM panel graded on
  full article text. A same-size non-reasoning-teacher control shows the summary gain
  follows from the teacher's reasoning nature, not its scale, and different teachers
  transfer different capabilities. Reports gap-closure toward the teacher, a localized
  short-source faithfulness effect, and a per-field engine-assignment map. Analysis
  reproduces offline from the released scorecard.
